http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Four-die-of-asphyxiation-as-they-enter-septic-tank-at-Chennai-hotel/article14006935.ece

Four persons, including three scavengers from the same family, died of asphyxiation when they entered a septic tank at the premises of a hotel in Karapakkam on Rajiv Gandhi Salai on Tuesday morning.Manuel scavenging has been banned by the State Government. According to the police, the incident took place around 9.30 a.m at Dindigul Thalapakatti Hotel. The victims are Saravanan, Kumar, Samiar alias Velmurugan and Rajesh. While Rajesh works as a delivery boy at the hotel, the other three are scavengers."Initially, Kumar went into the septic tank to clean it, as he did not return the others went in one after the other to check on his safety. Their bodies have been taken to the Government Royapettah Hospital for post mortem," said a police officer attached to Kannagi Nagar police station.A case has been registered and further investigation is on.